# Launch CaribbeanFreedomArena

When the user says **Preview**, **launch**, **open arena**, or **run from Desktop**, start the site from their saved copy.

## Desktop save (primary)

User database folder:

`~/Desktop/CARIBBEANLOVEAPP (DATA BASE)/caribbean-freedom-arena-website-*.zip`

After unzip (any of these):

```bash
cd ~/Desktop/CaribbeanFreedomArena
# or
cd ~/Desktop/CARIBBEANLOVEAPP\ \(DATA\ BASE\)/caribbean-freedom-arena-website
npm install          # first time only, or after unzip
npm run dev:arena
```

Or run: `./scripts/launch-caribbean-freedom-arena.sh` (auto-picks Desktop or repo)

**Preview URL:** http://localhost:3004/#home  
**Footer panel:** scroll to bottom  
**Hard refresh after updates:** `Cmd+Shift+R`

## This repo (development)

If working in `CARIBBEANLOVEAPP` instead of Desktop:

```bash
cd /Users/dimiphone/CARIBBEANLOVEAPP
npm run dev:arena
```

Same URL: http://localhost:3004/

## Rules

- Always use **`npm run dev:arena`** (clears `.next` first). Do not use plain `next dev` after a production build.
- If port 3004 is busy: `lsof -ti:3004 | xargs kill -9` then rerun `npm run dev:arena`.
- Production from Desktop: `npm run build:arena && npm run start:arena`
- Deliverable zip rebuild: `./scripts/build-website-deliverable.sh` → copies to **`~/Desktop/CARIBBEANLOVEAPP (DATA BASE)/`** and opens that folder in Finder (also saved in repo `deliverables/`)

## Unzip path

If the user unzipped `caribbean-freedom-arena-website-*.zip`, extract to:

- `~/Desktop/CaribbeanFreedomArena`, or
- `~/Desktop/CARIBBEANLOVEAPP (DATA BASE)/caribbean-freedom-arena-website`
